query.result:
**English:**
94 But he, who had come to my aid before, 95 perhaps for another reason, as soon as I mounted 96 embraced me with his arms and held me tight;
97 and he said: “Geryon, move now: 98 let your circles be wide, and your descent slow; 99 consider the new burden that you have”.
**Cornish:**
94 Mes ena, neb a-vynnys kovya kyns 95 rag aral, pan a-vynnas war’n geyn, 96 a-m golghas gans y vregh ha’m sevellas;
97 ha kovyas: “Geryon, kerdh bys vyth: 98 bydh an hweel lew, ha’n diskenn byghan; 99 meurydh an dowr nowyth a-wra vyth”.
